µJEI asked µC5RumrunnerµC4 to inform me as quickly as possible when the second edition of his diskmag would come out. And luckily after receiving his email and the mag itself as attachment, nobody else did already spread this production. So our sceneportal µC6Diskmag.deµC4 had the chance to do this officially. And beside, I could upload it to all bbs systems that are online until today and have an Amiga conference.

In his editorial µC5RumrunnerµC4 promised huge changes but unfortunately I could not discover many of them if I'm honest. Having the possibility to switch between the chiptunes by pressing F1 up to F3 is great. But else, my rusty eyes were not able to see any difference. Also the handling is still the same. And especially the menu-system is one of the weakest points of this mag. I always press the wrong arrow button and switch to the next article instead of getting to the next side of the article that I wanted to read.


